    7.4 Properties of Temporal.Duration Instances

    Temporal.Duration instances are ordinary objects that inherit properties from the %Temporal.Duration.prototype% intrinsic object. Temporal.Duration instances are initially created with the internal slots described in Table 7.

    7.5 Abstract Operations

    7.5.1 ToTemporalDuration ( item [ , constructor ] )

    The abstract operation ToTemporalDuration returns its argument item if it is already a Temporal.Duration instance, converts item to a new Temporal.Duration instance if possible, and throws otherwise.

    1. If constructor is not given, set it to %Temporal.Duration%.
    2. If Type(item) is Object, then
      1. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDuration]] internal slot, then
        1. Return item.
      2. Let result be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(item).
    3. Else,
      1. Let string be ? ToString(item).
      2. Let result be ? ParseTemporalDurationString(string).
    4. Return ? CreateTemporalDurationFromStatic(constructor, result.[[Years]], result.[[Months]], result.[[Weeks]], result.[[Days]], result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]], result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]], result.[[Nanoseconds]]).

    7.5.2 ToTemporalDurationRecord ( temporalDurationLike )

    Note
    The value of ? ToInteger(undefined) is 0.
    1. Assert: Type(temporalDurationLike) is Object.
    2. If temporalDurationLike has an [[InitializedTemporalDuration]] internal slot, then
      1. Return the Record { [[Years]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Years]], [[Months]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Months]], [[Weeks]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Weeks]], [[Days]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Days]], [[Hours]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Hours]], [[Minutes]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Minutes]], [[Seconds]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Seconds]], [[Milliseconds]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Milliseconds]], [[Microseconds]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Microseconds]], [[Nanoseconds]]: temporalDurationLike.[[Nanoseconds]] }.
    3. Let result be a new Record with all the internal slots given in the Internal Slot column in Table 8.
    4. Let any be false.
    5. For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do
      1. Let prop be the Property value of the current row.
      2. Let val be ? Get(temporalDurationLike, prop).
      3. If val is not undefined, then
        1. Set any to true.
      4. Let val be ? ToInteger(val).
      5. Set result's internal slot whose name is the Internal Slot value of the current row to val.
    6. If any is false, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    7. Return result.

    7.5.3 DurationSign ( years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds )

    1. For each value v of years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, do
      1. If v < 0, return 1.
      2. If v > 0, return 1.
    2. Return 0.

    7.5.4 RejectDurationSign ( years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds )

    1. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
    2. For each value v of years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, do
      1. If v < 0 and sign > 0, throw a RangeError exception.
      2. If v > 0 and sign < 0, throw a RangeError exception.

    7.5.5 ValidateTemporalDuration ( years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds )

    1. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
    2. For each value v of years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, do
      1. If v is infinite, return false.
      2. If v < 0 and sign > 0, return false.
      3. If v > 0 and sign < 0, return false.
    3. Return true.

    7.5.6 DefaultTemporalLargestUnit ( years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds )

    The abstract operation DefaultTemporalLargestUnit implements the logic used in the Temporal.Duration.prototype.round() method and elsewhere, where the largestUnit option, if not given explicitly, is set to the largest non-zero unit in the input Temporal.Duration.

    1. If years is not zero, return "years".
    2. If months is not zero, return "months".
    3. If weeks is not zero, return "weeks".
    4. If days is not zero, return "days".
    5. If hours is not zero, return "hours".
    6. If minutes is not zero, return "minutes".
    7. If seconds is not zero, return "seconds".
    8. If milliseconds is not zero, return "milliseconds".
    9. If microseconds is not zero, return "microseconds".
    10. Return "nanoseconds".

    7.5.7 ToPartialDuration ( temporalDurationLike )

    1. If Type(temporalDurationLike) is not Object, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    2. Let result be the new Record { [[Years]]: undefined, [[Months]]: undefined, [[Weeks]]: undefined, [[Days]]: undefined, [[Hours]]: undefined, [[Minutes]]: undefined, [[Seconds]]: undefined, [[Milliseconds]]: undefined, [[Microseconds]]: undefined, [[Nanoseconds]]: undefined }.
    3. Let any be false.
    4. For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do
      1. Let property be the Property value of the current row.
      2. Let value be ? Get(temporalDurationLike, property).
      3. If value is not undefined, then
        1. Set any to true.
        2. Set value to ? ToInteger(value).
        3. Set result's internal slot whose name is the Internal Slot value of the current row to value.
    5. If any is false, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    6. Return result.

    7.5.8 CreateTemporalDuration ( years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds [ , newTarget ] )

    1. If ! ValidateTemporalDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is false, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    2. If newTarget is not given, set it to %Temporal.Duration%.
    3. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget, "%Temporal.Duration.prototype%", [[InitializedTemporalDuration]], [[Years]], [[Months]], [[Weeks]], [[Days]], [[Hours]], [[Minutes]], [[Seconds]], [[Milliseconds]], [[Microseconds]], [[Nanoseconds]] ).
    4. Set object.[[Years]] to years.
    5. Set object.[[Months]] to months.
    6. Set object.[[Weeks]] to weeks.
    7. Set object.[[Days]] to days.
    8. Set object.[[Hours]] to hours.
    9. Set object.[[Minutes]] to minutes.
    10. Set object.[[Seconds]] to seconds.
    11. Set object.[[Milliseconds]] to milliseconds.
    12. Set object.[[Microseconds]] to microseconds.
    13. Set object.[[Nanoseconds]] to nanoseconds.
    14. Return object.

    7.5.9 CreateTemporalDurationFromInstance ( duration, years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds )

    1. Assert: Type(duration) is Object and duration has an [[InitializedTemporalDuration]] internal slot.
    2. Assert: ! ValidateDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is true.
    3. Let constructor be ? SpeciesConstructor(duration, %Temporal.Duration%).
    4. Let result be ? Construct(constructor, years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds ).
    5. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(result, [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]).
    6. Return result.

    7.5.10 CreateTemporalDurationFromStatic ( constructor, years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds )

    1. Assert: ! ValidateDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is true.
    2. If ! IsConstructor(constructor) is false, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    3. Let result be ? Construct(constructor, years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds ).
    4. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(result, [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]).
    5. Return result.

    7.5.11 BalanceDuration ( days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, largestUnit )

    1. Set hours to (hours) + (days) 24.
    2. Set minutes to (minutes) + hours 60.
    3. Set seconds to (seconds) + minutes 60.
    4. Set milliseconds to (milliseconds) + seconds 1000.
    5. Set microseconds to (microseconds) + milliseconds 1000.
    6. Set nanoseconds to (nanoseconds) + microseconds 1000.
    7. Set days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, and microseconds to 0.
    8. If nanoseconds < 0, let sign be 1; else, let sign be 1.
    9. Set nanoseconds to abs(nanoseconds).
    10. If largestUnit is "years", "months", "weeks", or "days", then
      1. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
      2. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
      3. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
      4. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
      5. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
      6. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
      7. Set minutes to floor(seconds / 60).
      8. Set seconds to seconds modulo 60.
      9. Set hours to floor(minutes / 60).
      10. Set minutes to minutes modulo 60.
      11. Set days to floor(hours / 24).
      12. Set hours to hours modulo 24.
    11. Else if largestUnit is "hours", then
      1. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
      2. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
      3. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
      4. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
      5. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
      6. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
      7. Set minutes to floor(seconds / 60).
      8. Set seconds to seconds modulo 60.
      9. Set hours to floor(minutes / 60).
      10. Set minutes to minutes modulo 60.
    12. Else if largestUnit is "minutes", then
      1. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
      2. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
      3. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
      4. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
      5. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
      6. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
      7. Set minutes to floor(seconds / 60).
      8. Set seconds to seconds modulo 60.
    13. Else if largestUnit is "seconds", then
      1. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
      2. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
      3. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
      4. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
      5. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
      6. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
    14. Else if largestUnit is "milliseconds", then
      1. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
      2. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
      3. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
      4. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
    15. Else if largestUnit is "microseconds", then
      1. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
      2. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
    16. Else,
      1. Assert: largestUnit is "nanoseconds".
    17. Return the new Record { [[Days]]: (days) sign, [[Hours]]: (hours) sign, [[Minutes]]: (minutes) sign, [[Seconds]]: (seconds) sign, [[Milliseconds]]: (milliseconds) sign, [[Microseconds]]: (microseconds) sign, [[Nanoseconds]]: (nanoseconds) sign }.

    7.5.12 UnbalanceDurationRelative ( years, months, weeks, days, largestUnit, relativeTo )

    The abstract operation UnbalanceDurationRelative converts the calendar units of a Temporal.Duration into a form where no unit is larger than largestUnit.

    1. If largestUnit is "years", or years, months, weeks, and days are all 0, then
      1. Return the new Record { [[Years]]: years, [[Months]]: months, [[Weeks]]: weeks, [[Days]]: days }.
    2. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    3. Assert: sign 0.
    4. Let oneYear be ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    5. Let oneMonth be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    6. Let oneWeek be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    7. Let addOptions be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
    8. If relativeTo is not undefined, then
      1. Assert: relativeTo has a [[Calendar]] internal slot.
      2. Let calendar be relativeTo.[[Calendar]].
    9. Else,
      1. Let calendar be undefined.
    10. If largestUnit is "months", then
      1. If calendaris undefined, then
        1. Throw a RangeError exception.
      2. Let dateAdd be ? Get(calendar, "dateAdd").
      3. Let dateUntil be ? Get(calendar, "dateUntil").
      4. Let untilOptions be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
      5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(untilOptions, "largestUnit", "months").
      6. Repeat, while abs(years) > 0,
        1. Let newRelativeTo be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, oneYear, addOptions, %Temporal.Date% ).
        2. Let untilResult be ? Call(dateUntil, calendar, relativeTo, newRelativeTo, untilOptions ).
        3. Let oneYearMonths be ? Get(untilResult, "months").
        4. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
        5. Set years to years sign.
        6. Set months to months + oneYearMonths.
    11. Else if largestUnit is "weeks", then
      1. If calendar is undefined, then
        1. Throw a RangeError exception.
      2. Repeat, while abs(years) > 0,
        1. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear).
        2. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        3. Set oneYearDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
        4. Set years to years sign.
        5. Set days to days + oneYearDays.
      3. Repeat, while abs(months) > 0,
        1. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneMonth).
        2. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        3. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
        4. Set months to months sign.
        5. Set days to days + oneMonthDays.
    12. Else,
      1. If any of years, months, and days are not zero, then
        1. If calendar is undefined, then
          1. Throw a RangeError exception.
        2. Repeat, while abs(years) > 0,
          1. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear).
          2. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
          3. Set oneYearDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
          4. Set years to years sign.
          5. Set days to days + oneYearDays.
        3. Repeat, while abs(months) > 0,
          1. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneMonth).
          2. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
          3. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
          4. Set months to months sign.
          5. Set days to days + oneMonthDays.
        4. Repeat, while abs(weeks) > 0,
          1. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneWeek).
          2. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
          3. Set oneWeekDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
          4. Set weeks to weeks sign.
          5. Set days to days + oneWeekDays.
    13. Return the new Record { [[Years]]: years, [[Months]]: months, [[Weeks]]: weeks, [[Days]]: days }.

    7.5.13 BalanceDurationRelative ( years, months, weeks, days, largestUnit, relativeTo )

    The abstract operation BalanceDurationRelative converts the calendar units of a duration into a form where lower units are converted into higher units as much as possible, up to largestUnit.

    1. If largestUnit is not one of "years", "months", or "weeks", or years, months, weeks, and days are all 0, then
      1. Return the new Record { [[Years]]: years, [[Months]]: months, [[Weeks]]: weeks, [[Days]]: days }.
    2. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    3. Assert: sign 0.
    4. Let oneYear be ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    5. Let oneMonth be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    6. Let oneWeek be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    7. If relativeTo is undefined, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    8. Assert: relativeTo has a [[Calendar]] internal slot.
    9. Let calendar be relativeTo.[[Calendar]].
    10. If largestUnit is "years", then
      1. Let dateAdd be ? Get(calendar, "dateAdd").
      2. Let addOptions be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
      3. Let dateUntil be ? Get(calendar, "dateUntil").
      4. Let untilOptions be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
      5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(untilOptions, "largestUnit", "months").
      6. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneYear).
      7. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      8. Let oneYearDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      9. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneYearDays),
        1. Set days to days oneYearDays.
        2. Set years to years + sign.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneYear).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneYearDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
      10. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneMonth).
      11. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      12. Let oneMonthDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      13. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneMonthDays),
        1. Set days to days oneMonthDays.
        2. Set months to months + sign.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneMonth).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
      14. Let newRelativeTo be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, oneYear, addOptions, %Temporal.Date% ).
      15. Let untilResult be ? Call(dateUntil, calendar, relativeTo, newRelativeTo, untilOptions ).
      16. Let oneYearMonths be ? Get(untilResult, "months").
      17. Repeat, while abs(months) abs(oneYearMonths),
        1. Set months to months oneYearMonths.
        2. Set years to years + sign.
        3. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
        4. Set newRelativeTo to ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, oneYear, addOptions, %Temporal.Date% ).
        5. Set untilResult to ? Call(dateUntil, calendar, relativeTo, newRelativeTo, untilOptions ).
        6. Set oneYearMonths to ? Get(untilResult, "months").
    11. Else if largestUnit is "months", then
      1. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneMonth).
      2. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      3. Let oneMonthDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      4. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneMonthDays),
        1. Set days to days oneMonthDays.
        2. Set months to months + sign.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneMonth).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
    12. Else,
      1. Assert: largestUnit is "weeks".
      2. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneWeek).
      3. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      4. Let oneWeekDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      5. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneWeekDays),
        1. Set days to days oneWeekDays.
        2. Set weeks to weeks + sign.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, _relativeTo, oneWeek).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneWeekDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
    13. Return the new Record { [[Years]]: years, [[Months]]: months, [[Weeks]]: weeks, [[Days]]: days }.

    7.5.14 AddDuration ( y1, mon1, w1, d1, h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1, ns1, y2, mon2, w2, d2, h2, min2, s2, ms2, mus2, ns2 )

    The abstract operation AddDuration adds the components of a second duration to those of a first duration, and balances the duration to ensure that no mixed signs remain in the result (or throws a RangeError if that is not possible).

    1. Assert: y1, mon1, w1, d1, h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1, ns1, y2, mon2, w2, d2, h2, min2, s2, ms2, mus2, ns2 are integer Number values.
    2. Let nanoseconds be ns1 + ns2.
    3. Let microseconds be mus1 + mus2.
    4. Let milliseconds be ms1 + ms2.
    5. Let seconds be s1 + s2.
    6. Let minutes be min1 + min2.
    7. Let hours be h1 + h2.
    8. Let days be d1 + d2.
    9. Let weeks be w1 + w2.
    10. Let months be mon1 + mon2.
    11. Let years be y1 + y2.
    12. Let largestUnit be ! DefaultTemporalLargestUnit(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
    13. Let balanceResult be ? BalanceDuration(days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, largestUnit).
    14. Set days to balanceResult.[[Days]].
    15. Set hours to balanceResult.[[Hours]].
    16. Set minutes to balanceResult.[[Minutes]].
    17. Set seconds to balanceResult.[[Seconds]].
    18. Set milliseconds to balanceResult.[[Milliseconds]].
    19. Set microseconds to balanceResult.[[Microseconds]].
    20. Set nanoseconds to balanceResult.[[Nanoseconds]].
    21. If ! ValidateDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is false, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    22. Return the new Record { [[Years]]: years, [[Months]]: months, [[Weeks]]: weeks, [[Days]]: days, [[Hours]]: hours, [[Minutes]]: minutes, [[Seconds]]: seconds, [[Milliseconds]]: milliseconds, [[Microseconds]]: microseconds, [[Nanoseconds]]: nanoseconds }.

    7.5.15 DaysUntil ( earlier, later )

    The abstract operation DaysUntil returns the integer number of days elapsed between the calendar dates of two Temporal object instances earlier and later. If earlier is later than later, then the result is a negative integer.

    1. Assert: earlier and later both have [[ISOYear]], [[ISOMonth]], and [[ISODay]] internal slots.
    2. Let difference be ? DifferenceDate(earlier.[[ISOYear]], earlier.[[ISOMonth]], earlier.[[ISODay]], later.[[ISOYear]], later.[[ISOMonth]], later.[[ISODay]], "days").
    3. Return difference.[[Days]].

    7.5.16 MoveRelativeDate ( calendar, relativeTo, duration )

    The abstract operation MoveRelativeDate takes a Temporal.Date object relativeTo, and adds a Temporal.Duration duration to it, returning a record with the result as well as the number of days added according to the calendar reckoning of calendar. This is used when balancing or rounding durations relative to a particular date.

    1. Let dateAdd be ? Get(calendar, "dateAdd").
    2. Let options be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
    3. Let later be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, duration, options, %Temporal.Date% ).
    4. Let days be ? DaysUntil(relativeTo, later).
    5. Return the new Record { [[RelativeTo]]: later, [[Days]]: days }.

    7.5.17 RoundDuration ( years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, increment, unit, roundingMode [ , relativeTo ] )

    1. Let years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, and increment each be the mathematical values of themselves.
    2. If unit is "years", "months", or "weeks", then
      1. If relativeTo is not given, then
        1. Throw a RangeError exception.
      2. Else,
        1. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(relativeTo, [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]).
        2. Let calendar be relativeTo.[[Calendar]].
        3. Let dateAdd be ? Get(calendar, "dateAdd").
        4. Let options be ? ObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
    3. Let fractionalSeconds be nanoseconds 109 + microseconds 106 + milliseconds 103 + seconds.
    4. Let fractionalDays be ((fractionalSeconds / 60 + minutes) / 60 + hours) / 24 + days.
    5. Let remainder be undefined.
    6. If unit is "years", then
      1. Let yearsDuration be ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      2. Let yearsLater be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, yearsDuration, options, %Temporal.Date%).
      3. Let yearsMonthsWeeks be ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, months, weeks, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      4. Let yearsMonthsWeeksLater be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, yearsMonthsWeeks, options, %Temporal.Date%).
      5. Let monthsWeeksInDays be ? DaysUntil(yearsLater, yearsMonthsWeeksLater).
      6. Set relativeTo to yearsLater.
      7. Let days be days + monthsWeeksInDays..
      8. Let sign be ! Sign(days).
      9. If sign is 0, set sign to 1.
      10. Let oneYear be ? CreateTemporalDuration(sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      11. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear).
      12. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      13. Let oneYearDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      14. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneYearDays),
        1. Set years to years + sign.
        2. Set days to days oneYearDays.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneYearDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
      15. Let fractionalYears be years + days / abs(oneYearDays).
      16. Set years to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalYears, increment, roundingMode).
      17. Set remainder to fractionalYears - years.
      18. Set months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    7. Else if unit is "months", then
      1. Let yearsMonths be ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, months, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      2. Let yearsMonthsLater be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, yearsMonths, options, %Temporal.Date%).
      3. Let yearsMonthsWeeks be ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, months, weeks, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      4. Let yearsMonthsWeeksLater be ? Call(dateAdd, calendar, relativeTo, yearsMonthsWeeks, options, %Temporal.Date%).
      5. Let weeksInDays be ? DaysUntil(yearsMonthsLater, yearsMonthsWeeksLater).
      6. Set relativeTo to yearsMonthsLater.
      7. Let days be days + weeksInDays.
      8. Let sign be ! Sign(days).
      9. If sign is 0, set sign to 1.
      10. Let oneMonth be ? CreateTemporalDuration(0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      11. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneMonth).
      12. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      13. Let oneMonthDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      14. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneMonthDays),
        1. Set months to months + sign.
        2. Set days to days oneMonthDays.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneMonth).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
      15. Let fractionalMonths be months + days / abs(oneMonthDays).
      16. Set months to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalMonths, increment, roundingMode).
      17. Set remainder to fractionalMonths - months.
      18. Set weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    8. Else if unit is "weeks", then
      1. Let sign be ! Sign(days).
      2. If sign is 0, set sign to 1.
      3. Let oneWeek be ? CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
      4. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneWeek).
      5. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
      6. Let oneWeekDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
      7. Repeat, while abs(days) abs(oneWeekDays),
        1. Set weeks to weeks + sign.
        2. Set days to days oneWeekDays.
        3. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneWeek).
        4. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
        5. Set oneWeekDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
      8. Let fractionalWeeks be weeks + fractionalDays / abs(oneWeekDays).
      9. Set weeks to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalWeeks, increment, roundingMode).
      10. Set remainder to fractionalWeeks - weeks.
      11. Set days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    9. Else if unit is "days", then
      1. Set days to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalDays, increment, roundingMode).
      2. Set remainder to fractionalDays - days.
      3. Set hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    10. Else if unit is "hours", then
      1. Let fractionalHours be (fractionalSeconds / 60 + minutes) / 60 + hours.
      2. Set hours to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalHours, increment, roundingMode).
      3. Set remainder to fractionalHours - hours.
      4. Set minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    11. Else if unit is "minutes", then
      1. Let fractionalMinutes be fractionalSeconds / 60 + minutes.
      2. Set minutes to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalMinutes, increment, roundingMode).
      3. Set remainder to fractionalMinutes - minutes.
      4. Set seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    12. Else if unit is "seconds", then
      1. Set seconds to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalSeconds, increment, roundingMode).
      2. Set remainder to fractionalSeconds - seconds.
      3. Set milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds to 0.
    13. Else if unit is "milliseconds", then
      1. Let fractionalMilliseconds be nanoseconds 106 + microseconds 103 + milliseconds.
      2. Set milliseconds to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalMilliseconds, increment, roundingMode).
      3. Set remainder to fractionalMilliseconds - milliseconds.
      4. Set microseconds and nanoseconds to 0.
    14. Else if unit is "microseconds", then
      1. Let fractionalMicroseconds be nanoseconds 103 + microseconds.
      2. Set microseconds to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(fractionalMicroseconds, increment, roundingMode).
      3. Set remainder to fractionalMicroseconds - microseconds.
      4. Set nanoseconds to 0.
    15. Else,
      1. Assert: unit is "nanoseconds".
      2. Set remainder to 0.
      3. Set nanoseconds to ? RoundNumberToIncrement(nanoseconds, increment, roundingMode).
    16. Return the new Record { [[Years]]: years, [[Months]]: months, [[Weeks]]: weeks, [[Days]]: days, [[Hours]]: hours, [[Minutes]]: minutes, [[Seconds]]: seconds, [[Milliseconds]]: milliseconds, [[Microseconds]]: microseconds, [[Nanoseconds]]: nanoseconds, [[Remainder]]: remainder }.

    7.5.18 ToLimitedTemporalDuration ( temporalDurationLike, disallowedFields )

    1. If Type(temporalDurationLike) is not Object, then
      1. Let str be ? ToString(temporalDurationLike).
      2. Let duration be ? ParseTemporalDurationString(str).
    2. Else,
      1. Let duration be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(temporalDurationLike).
    3. If ! ValidateTemporalDuration(duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]], duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]], duration.[[Nanoseconds]]) is false, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    4. For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do
      1. Let prop be the Property value of the current row.
      2. Let value be duration's internal slot whose name is the Internal Slot value of the current row.
      3. If value is not 0 and disallowedFields contains prop, then
        1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    5. Return duration.

    7.5.19 TemporalDurationToString ( duration )

    1. Let years be duration.[[Years]].
    2. Let months be duration.[[Months]].
    3. Let weeks be duration.[[Weeks]].
    4. Let days be duration.[[Days]].
    5. Let hours duration.[[Hours]].
    6. Let minutes duration.[[Minutes]].
    7. Let seconds be the mathematical value of duration.[[Seconds]].
    8. Let milliseconds be the mathematical value of duration.[[Milliseconds]].
    9. Let microseconds be the mathematical value of duration.[[Microseconds]].
    10. Let nanoseconds be the mathematical value of duration.[[Nanoseconds]].
    11. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
    12. Set microseconds to microseconds + the integral part of nanoseconds / 1000.
    13. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
    14. Set milliseconds to milliseconds + the integral part of microseconds / 1000.
    15. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
    16. Set seconds to seconds + the integral part of milliseconds / 1000.
    17. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
    18. If years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds are all 0, then
      1. Return the string "PT0S".
    19. Let datePart be "".
    20. If years is not 0, then
      1. Set datePart to the string concatenation of abs(years) formatted as a decimal number and the code unit 0x0059 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER Y).
    21. If months is not 0, then
      1. Set datePart to the string concatenation of datePart, abs(months) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit 0x004D (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER M).
    22. If weeks is not 0, then
      1. Set datePart to the string concatenation of datePart, abs(weeks) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit 0x0057 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER W).
    23. If days is not 0, then
      1. Set datePart to the string concatenation of datePart, abs(days) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit 0x0044 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER D).
    24. Let timePart be "".
    25. If hours is not 0, then
      1. Set timePart to the string concatenation of abs(hours) formatted as a decimal number and the code unit 0x0048 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER H).
    26. If minutes is not 0, then
      1. Set timePart to the string concatenation of timePart, abs(minutes) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit 0x004D (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER M).
    27. If any of seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds are not 0, then
      1. Let nanosecondsPart, microsecondsPart, and millisecondsPart be "".
      2. If nanoseconds is not 0, then
        1. Set nanosecondsPart to nanoseconds formatted as a three-digit decimal number, padded to the left with zeroes if necessary.
        2. Set microsecondsPart and millisecondsPart to "000".
      3. If microseconds is not 0, then
        1. Set microsecondsPart be microseconds formatted as a three-digit decimal number, padded to the left with zeroes if necessary.
        2. Set millisecondsPart to "000".
      4. If milliseconds is not 0, then
        1. Set millisecondsPart to milliseconds formatted as a three-digit decimal number, padded to the left with zeroes if necessary.
      5. Let decimalPart be the string-concatenation of millisecondsPart, microsecondsPart, and nanosecondsPart.
      6. Let secondsPart be seconds formatted as a decimal number.
      7. If decimalPart is not "", then
        1. Set secondsPart to the string-concatenation of secondsPart, the code unit 0x002E (FULL STOP), and decimalPart.
      8. Set timePart to the string concatenation of timePart, secondsPart, and the code unit 0x0053 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER S).
    28. Let signPart be the code unit 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS) if sign < 0, and otherwise the empty String.
    29. Let result be the string concatenation of signPart, the code unit 0x0050 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER P) and datePart.
    30. If timePart is not "", then
      1. Set result to the string concatenation of result, the code unit 0x0054 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER T), timePart, and secondsPart.
    31. Return result.

    7.5.20 FormatDuration ( durationFormat, duration )

    1. Let record be ? ToPartialDuration(duration).
    2. Let formatted be ? PartitionDurationFormatPattern(df, record).
    3. Let result be the empty String.
    4. For each Record part in formatted, do
      1. Set result to the string-concatenation of result and part.[[Value]].
    5. Return result.

    8 Temporal.Instant Objects

    A Temporal.Instant object is an immutable Object referencing a point in time with nanoseconds precision.

    8.1 The Temporal.Instant Constructor

    The Temporal.Instant constructor is the %Temporal.Instant% intrinsic object. When called as a constructor, it creates and initializes a new Temporal.Instant object.

    The Temporal.Instant constructor is designed to be subclassable. It may be used as the value of an extends clause of a class definition. Subclass constructors that intend to inherit the specified Instant behaviour must include a super call to the %Temporal.Instant% constructor to create and initialize subclass instances with the necessary internal slots.

    8.1.1 Temporal.Instant ( epochNanoseconds )

    When the Temporal.Instant function is called, the following steps are taken:

    1. If NewTarget is undefined, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    2. Let epochNanoseconds be ? ToBigInt(epochNanoseconds).
    3. Perform ? RejectInstant(epochNanoseconds).
    4. Return ? CreateTemporalInstant(epochNanoseconds, NewTarget).

    8.2 Properties of the Temporal.Instant Constructor

    The value of the [[Prototype]] internal slot of the Temporal.Instant constructor is the intrinsic object %Function.prototype%.

    The Temporal.Instant constructor has the following properties:

    8.2.1 Temporal.Instant.prototype

    The initial value of Temporal.Instant.prototype is %Temporal.Instant.prototype%.

    This property has the attributes { [[Writable]]: false, [[Enumerable]]: false, [[Configurable]]: false }.

    8.2.2 get Temporal.Instant [ @@species ]

    Temporal.Instant[@@species] is an accessor property whose set accessor function is undefined. Its get accessor function performs the following steps:

    1. Return the this value.

    The value of the "name" property of this function is "get [Symbol.species]".

    8.2.3 Temporal.Instant.from ( item )

    The from method takes one argument item. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let constructor be the this value.
    2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot, then
      1. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic(constructor, item.[[Nanoseconds]]).
    3. Return ? ToTemporalInstant(item, constructor).

    8.2.4 Temporal.Instant.fromEpochSeconds ( epochSeconds )

    The fromEpochSeconds method takes one argument epochSeconds. The following steps are taken:

    1. Set epochSeconds to ? ToNumber(epochSeconds).
    2. Set epochSeconds to ? NumberToBigInt(epochSeconds).
    3. Let epochNanoseconds be epochSeconds 1,000,000,000.
    4. Perform ? RejectInstant(epochNanoseconds).
    5. Let constructor be the this value.
    6. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic(constructor, epochNanoseconds).

    8.2.5 Temporal.Instant.fromEpochMilliseconds ( epochMilliseconds )

    The fromEpochMilliseconds method takes one argument epochMilliseconds. The following steps are taken:

    1. Set epochMilliseconds to ? ToNumber(epochMilliseconds).
    2. Set epochMilliseconds to ? NumberToBigInt(epochMilliseconds).
    3. Let epochNanoseconds be epochMilliseconds 1,000,000.
    4. Perform ? RejectInstant(epochNanoseconds).
    5. Let constructor be the this value.
    6. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic(constructor, epochNanoseconds).

    8.2.6 Temporal.Instant.fromEpochMicroseconds ( epochMicroseconds )

    The fromEpochMicroseconds method takes one argument epochMicroseconds. The following steps are taken:

    1. Set epochMicroseconds to ? ToBigInt(epochMicroseconds).
    2. Let epochNanoseconds be epochMicroseconds 1,000.
    3. Perform ? RejectInstant(epochNanoseconds).
    4. Let constructor be the this value.
    5. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic(constructor, epochNanoseconds).

    8.2.7 Temporal.Instant.fromEpochNanoseconds ( epochNanoseconds )

    The fromEpochNanoseconds method takes one argument epochNanoseconds. The following steps are taken:

    1. Set epochNanoseconds to ? ToBigInt(epochNanoseconds).
    2. Perform ? RejectInstant(epochNanoseconds).
    3. Let constructor be the this value.
    4. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic(constructor, epochNanoseconds).

    8.2.8 Temporal.Instant.compare ( one, two )

    The compare method takes two arguments, one and two. The following steps are taken:

    1. Set one to ? ToTemporalInstant(one).
    2. Set two to ? ToTemporalInstant(two).
    3. Return (! CompareEpochNanoseconds(one.[[Nanoseconds]], two.[[Nanoseconds]])).

    8.3 Properties of the Temporal.Instant Prototype Object

    The Temporal.Instant prototype object

    • is the intrinsic object %Temporal.Instant.prototype%.
    • is itself an ordinary object.
    • is not a Temporal.Instant instance and does not have a [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot.
    • has a [[Prototype]] internal slot whose value is %Object.prototype%.

    8.3.1 Temporal.Instant.prototype.constructor

    The initial value of Temporal.Instant.prototype.constructor is %Temporal.Instant%.

    8.3.2 Temporal.Instant.prototype[ @@toStringTag ]

    The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string value "Temporal.Instant".

    This property has the attributes { [[Writable]]: false, [[Enumerable]]: false, [[Configurable]]: true }.

    8.3.3 get Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochSeconds

    Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochSeconds is an accessor property whose set accessor function is undefined. Its get accessor function performs the following steps:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let ns be instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    4. Let s be RoundTowardsZero((ns) / 1,000,000,000).
    5. Return (s).

    8.3.4 get Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochMilliseconds

    Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochMilliseconds is an accessor property whose set accessor function is undefined. Its get accessor function performs the following steps:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let ns be instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    4. Let ms be RoundTowardsZero((ns) / 1,000,000).
    5. Return (ms).

    8.3.5 get Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochMicroseconds

    Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochMicroseconds is an accessor property whose set accessor function is undefined. Its get accessor function performs the following steps:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let ns be instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    4. Let s be RoundTowardsZero((ns) / 1,000).
    5. Return (s).

    8.3.6 get Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochNanoseconds

    Temporal.Instant.prototype.epochNanoseconds is an accessor property whose set accessor function is undefined. Its get accessor function performs the following steps:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let ns be instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    4. Return ns.

    8.3.7 Temporal.Instant.prototype.add ( temporalDurationLike )

    The add method takes one argument temporalDurationLike. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let duration be ? ToLimitedTemporalDuration(temporalDurationLike, "years", "months", "weeks", "days" ).
    4. Perform ? RejectDurationSign(duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]], duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]], duration.[[Nanoseconds]]).
    5. Let ns be instant.[[Nanoseconds]] + duration.[[Nanoseconds]] + duration.[[Microseconds]] 1000 + duration.[[Milliseconds]] 1,000,000 + duration.[[Seconds]] 1,000,000,000 + duration.[[Minutes]] 60,000,000,000 + duration.[[Hours]] 3,600,000,000,000.
    6. Perform ? RejectInstant(ns).
    7. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromInstance(instant, ns).

    8.3.8 Temporal.Instant.prototype.subtract ( temporalDurationLike )

    The subtract method takes one argument temporalDurationLike. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let duration be ? ToLimitedTemporalDuration(temporalDurationLike, "years", "months", "weeks", "days" ).
    4. Perform ? RejectDurationSign(duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]], duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]], duration.[[Nanoseconds]]).
    5. Let ns be instant.[[Nanoseconds]] duration.[[Nanoseconds]] duration.[[Microseconds]] 1000 duration.[[Milliseconds]] 1,000,000 duration.[[Seconds]] 1,000,000,000 duration.[[Minutes]] 60,000,000,000 duration.[[Hours]] 3,600,000,000,000.
    6. Perform ? RejectInstant(ns).
    7. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromInstance(instant, ns).

    8.3.9 Temporal.Instant.prototype.until ( other [ , options ] )

    The until method takes two arguments, other and options. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Set other to ? ToTemporalInstant(other).
    4. Set options to ? NormalizeOptionsObject(options).
    5. Let smallestUnit be ? ToSmallestTemporalDurationUnit(options, "years", "months", "weeks", "days" , "nanoseconds").
    6. Let defaultLargestUnit be ! LargerOfTwoTemporalDurationUnits("seconds", smallestUnit).
    7. Let largestUnit be ? ToLargestTemporalUnit(options, "years", "months", "weeks", "days" , defaultLargestUnit).
    8. Perform ? ValidateTemporalUnitRange(largestUnit, smallestUnit).
    9. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "nearest").
    10. Let maximum be ! MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallestUnit).
    11. Let roundingIncrement be the mathematical value of ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(options, maximum, false).
    12. If smallestUnit is "hours", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 3.6 1012.
    13. If smallestUnit is "minutes", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 6 1010.
    14. Else if smallestUnit is "seconds", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 109.
    15. Else if smallestUnit is "milliseconds", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 106.
    16. Else if smallestUnit is "microseconds", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 103.
    17. Else,
      1. Assert: smallestUnit is "nanoseconds".
      2. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement.
    18. Let diff be the mathematical value of otherInstant.[[Nanoseconds]] instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    19. Let roundedNs be ? RoundNumberToIncrement(diff, incrementNs, roundingMode).
    20. Let result be ! BalanceDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, roundedNs, largestUnit).
    21. Return ? CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]], result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]], result.[[Nanoseconds]]).

    8.3.10 Temporal.Instant.prototype.since ( other [ , options ] )

    The since method takes two arguments, other and options. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Set other to ? ToTemporalInstant(other).
    4. Set options to ? NormalizeOptionsObject(options).
    5. Let smallestUnit be ? ToSmallestTemporalDurationUnit(options, "years", "months", "weeks", "days" , "nanoseconds").
    6. Let defaultLargestUnit be ! LargerOfTwoTemporalDurationUnits("seconds", smallestUnit).
    7. Let largestUnit be ? ToLargestTemporalUnit(options, "years", "months", "weeks", "days" , defaultLargestUnit).
    8. Perform ? ValidateTemporalUnitRange(largestUnit, smallestUnit).
    9. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "nearest").
    10. Let maximum be ! MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallestUnit).
    11. Let roundingIncrement be the mathematical value of ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(options, maximum, false).
    12. If smallestUnit is "hours", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 3.6 1012.
    13. If smallestUnit is "minutes", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 6 1010.
    14. Else if smallestUnit is "seconds", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 109.
    15. Else if smallestUnit is "milliseconds", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 106.
    16. Else if smallestUnit is "microseconds", then
      1. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement 103.
    17. Else,
      1. Assert: smallestUnit is "nanoseconds".
      2. Let incrementNs be roundingIncrement.
    18. Let diff be the mathematical value of instant.[[Nanoseconds]] otherInstant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    19. Let roundedNs be ? RoundNumberToIncrement(diff, incrementNs, roundingMode).
    20. Let result be ! BalanceDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, roundedNs, largestUnit).
    21. Return ? CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]], result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]], result.[[Nanoseconds]]).

    8.3.11 Temporal.Instant.prototype.round ( options )

    The round method takes one argument options. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Set options to ? NormalizeOptionsObject(options).
    4. Let smallestUnit be ? ToSmallestTemporalUnit(options, "day" ).
    5. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "nearest").
    6. If smallestUnit is "hour", then
      1. Let maximum be 24.
    7. Else if smallestUnit is "minute", then
      1. Let maximum be 1440.
    8. Else if smallestUnit is "second", then
      1. Let maximum be 86400.
    9. Else if smallestUnit is "millisecond", then
      1. Let maximum be 8.64 107.
    10. Else if smallestUnit is "microsecond", then
      1. Let maximum be 8.64 1010.
    11. Else,
      1. Assert: smallestUnit is "nanosecond".
      2. Let maximum be 8.64 1013.
    12. Let roundingIncrement be the mathematical value of ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(options, maximum, true).
    13. Let ns be the mathematical value of instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    14. Let roundedNs be ? RoundTemporalInstant(ns, roundingIncrement, smallestUnit, roundingMode).
    15. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromInstance(instant, roundedNs).

    8.3.12 Temporal.Instant.prototype.equals ( other )

    The equals method takes one argument other. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Set other to ? ToTemporalInstant(other).
    4. If instant.[[Nanoseconds]] other.[[Nanoseconds]], return false.
    5. Return true.

    8.3.13 Temporal.Instant.prototype.toString ( [ temporalTimeZoneLike [ , options ] ] )

    The toString method takes two arguments, temporalTimeZoneLike and options. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Set options to ? NormalizeOptionsObject(options).
    4. Let precision be ? ToFractionalSecondDigits(options).
    5. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "trunc").
    6. Let ns be the mathematical value of instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
    7. Let roundedNs be ? RoundTemporalInstant(ns, precision.[[Increment]], precision.[[Unit]], roundingMode).
    8. Let roundedInstant be ? CreateTemporalInstant(roundedNs).
    9. If temporalTimeZoneLike is undefined, then
      1. Set temporalTimeZoneLike to "UTC".
    10. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(temporalTimeZoneLike).
    11. Let calendar be ? GetISO8601Calendar().
    12. Return ? TemporalInstantToString(roundedInstant, timeZone, calendar, precision.[[Precision]]).

    8.3.14 Temporal.Instant.prototype.toLocaleString ( [ locales [ , options ] ] )

    The toLocaleString method takes two arguments, locales and options. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. If the implementation does not include the ECMA-402 Internationalization API, then
      1. Let timeZone be ? CreateTemporalTimeZone("UTC").
      2. Let calendar be ? GetISO8601Calendar().
      3. Return ? TemporalInstantToString(instant, timeZone, calendar, "auto").
    4. Let dateFormat be ? Construct(%DateTimeFormat%, locales, options ).
    5. Return ? FormatDateTime(dateFormat, instant).

    8.3.15 Temporal.Instant.prototype.toJSON ( )

    The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let timeZone be ? CreateTemporalTimeZone("UTC").
    4. Let calendar be ? GetISO8601Calendar().
    5. Return ? TemporalInstantToString(instant, timeZone, calendar, "auto").

    8.3.16 Temporal.Instant.prototype.valueOf ( )

    The following steps are taken:

    1. Throw a TypeError exception.

    8.3.17 Temporal.Instant.prototype.toZonedDateTime ( temporalTimeZoneLike, calendarLike )

    The toZonedDateTime method takes two arguments, temporalTimeZoneLike and calendarLike. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(temporalTimeZoneLike).
    4. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendar(calendarLike).
    5. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(instant.[[Nanoseconds]], timeZone, calendar).

    8.3.18 Temporal.Instant.prototype.toZonedDateTimeISO ( temporalTimeZoneLike )

    The toZonedDateTimeISO method takes one argument temporalTimeZoneLike. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let instant be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(instant, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    3. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(temporalTimeZoneLike).
    4. Let calendar be ? GetISO8601Calendar().
    5. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(instant.[[Nanoseconds]], timeZone, calendar).

    8.4 Properties of Temporal.Instant Instances

    Temporal.Instant instances are ordinary objects that inherit properties from the %Temporal.Instant.prototype% intrinsic object. Temporal.Instant instances are initially created with the internal slots described in Table 9.

    8.5 Abstract operations

    8.5.1 ValidateInstant ( ns )

    1. Assert: Type(ns) is BigInt.
    2. If ns < 8.64 1021 or ns > 8.64 1021, then
      1. Return false.
    3. Return true.

    8.5.2 RejectInstant ( ns )

    1. Assert: Type(ns) is BigInt.
    2. If ! ValidateInstant(ns) is false, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.

    8.5.3 CreateTemporalInstant ( ns [ , newTarget ] )

    1. Assert: Type(ns) is BigInt.
    2. Assert: ! ValidateInstant(ns) is true.
    3. If newTarget is not given, set it to %Temporal.Instant%.
    4. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget, "%Temporal.Instant.prototype%", [[InitializedTemporalInstant]], [[Nanoseconds]] ).
    5. Set object.[[Nanoseconds]] to ns.
    6. Return object.

    8.5.4 CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic ( constructor, ns )

    1. Assert: ! ValidateInstant(ns) is true.
    2. If ! IsConstructor(constructor) is false, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    3. Let result be ? Construct(constructor, ns ).
    4. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(result, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    5. Return result.

    8.5.5 CreateTemporalInstantFromInstance ( instant, ns )

    1. Assert: Type(instant) is Object and instant has an [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot.
    2. Assert: ! ValidateInstant(ns) is true.
    3. Let constructor be ? SpeciesConstructor(instant, %Temporal.Instant%).
    4. Let result be ? Construct(constructor, ns ).
    5. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(result, [[InitializedTemporalInstant]]).
    6. Return result.

    8.5.6 ToTemporalInstant ( item [ , constructor ] )

    The abstract operation ToTemporalInstant returns its argument item if it is already a Temporal.Instant instance, converts item to a new Temporal.Instant instance if possible, and throws otherwise.

    1. If constructor is not given, set it to %Temporal.Instant%.
    2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot, then
      1. Return item.
    3. Let string be ? ToString(item).
    4. Let epochNanoseconds be ? ParseTemporalInstant(string).
    5. Return ? CreateTemporalInstantFromStatic(constructor, epochNanoseconds).

    8.5.7 ParseTemporalInstant ( isoString )

    1. Assert: Type(isoString) is String.
    2. Let result be ? ParseTemporalInstantString(isoString).
    3. Let offsetString be result.[[TimeZoneOffsetString]].
    4. If offsetString is undefined, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    5. Let utc be ? GetEpochFromParts(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]], result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]]).
    6. If utc < 8.64 1021 or utc > 8.64 1021, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    7. Let offsetNanoseconds be ? ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(offsetString).
    8. Return utc offsetNanoseconds.

    8.5.8 CompareEpochNanoseconds ( epochNanosecondsOne, epochNanosecondsTwo )

    1. If epochNanosecondsOne > epochNanosecondsTwo, return 1.
    2. If epochNanosecondsOne < epochNanosecondsTwo, return -1.
    3. Return 0.

    8.5.9 RoundTemporalInstant ( ns, increment, unit, roundingMode )

    The abstract operation RoundTemporalInstant rounds a number of nanoseconds since the Unix epoch to the given rounding increment.

    1. If unit is "hour", then
      1. Let incrementNs be increment 3.6 1012.
    2. Else if unit is "minute", then
      1. Let incrementNs be increment 6 1010.
    3. Else if unit is "second", then
      1. Let incrementNs be increment 109.
    4. Else if unit is "millisecond", then
      1. Let incrementNs be increment 106.
    5. Else if unit is "microsecond", then
      1. Let incrementNs be increment 103.
    6. Else,
      1. Let incrementNs be increment.
    7. Return ? RoundNumberToIncrement(ns, incrementNs, roundingMode).

    8.5.10 TemporalInstantToString ( instant, timeZone, calendar, precision )

    1. Assert: Type(instant) is Object.
    2. Assert: instant has an [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot.
    3. Let dateTime be ? GetTemporalDateTimeFor(timeZone, instant, calendar).
    4. Let dateTimeString be ? TemporalDateTimeToString(dateTime.[[ISOYear]], dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[Hour]], dateTime.[[Minute]], dateTime.[[Second]], dateTime.[[Millisecond]], dateTime.[[Microsecond]], dateTime.[[Nanosecond]], precision).
    5. Let timeZoneString be ? ISOTimeZoneString(timeZone, instant).
    6. Return the string-concatenation of dateTimeString and timeZoneString.

    8.5.11 ISOTimeZoneString ( instant, timeZone )

    1. Assert: Type(instant) is Object.
    2. Assert: instant has an [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot.
    3. Assert?: Type(timeZone) is Object.
    4. Let name be ? TimeZoneToString(timeZone).
    5. Let offset be ? GetOffsetStringFor(timeZone, instant).
    6. If name is "UTC", then
      1. Return "Z".
    7. If name is offset, then
      1. Return offset.
    8. Return the string-concatenation of offset, "[", name, and "]".

    9 Temporal.YearMonth Objects

    A Temporal.YearMonth object is an immutable Object that contains Number values corresponding to a particular year and month.

    9.1 The Temporal.YearMonth Constructor

    The Temporal.YearMonth constructor is the %Temporal.YearMonth% intrinsic object. When called as a constructor, it creates and initializes a new Temporal.YearMonth object.

    The Temporal.YearMonth constructor is designed to be subclassable. It may be used as the value of an extends clause of a class definition. Subclass constructors that intend to inherit the specified YearMonth behaviour must include a super call to the %Temporal.YearMonth% constructor to create and initialize subclass instances with the necessary internal slots.

    9.1.1 Temporal.YearMonth ( isoYear, isoMonth [ , calendarLike [ , referenceISODay ] ] )

    When the Temporal.YearMonth function is called, the following steps are taken:

    1. If NewTarget is undefined, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    2. If referenceISODay is undefined, then
      1. Set referenceISODay to 1.
    3. Let y be ? ToInteger(isoYear).
    4. Let m be ? ToInteger(isoMonth).
    5. If calendarLike is undefined, then
      1. Set calendar to ? GetISO8601Calendar().
    6. Else,
      1. Set calendar to ? ToTemporalCalendar(calendarLike).
    7. Let ref be ? ToInteger(referenceISODay).
    8. Return ? CreateTemporalYearMonth(y, m, calendar, ref, NewTarget).

    9.4 Properties of Temporal.YearMonth Instances

    Temporal.YearMonth instances are ordinary objects that inherit properties from the %Temporal.YearMonth.prototype% intrinsic object. Temporal.YearMonth instances are initially created with the internal slots described in Table 10.

    9.5 Abstract operations

    9.5.1 ToTemporalYearMonth ( item [ , constructor [ , overflow ] ] )

    The abstract operation ToTemporalYearMonth returns its argument item if it is already a Temporal.YearMonth instance, converts item to a new Temporal.YearMonth instance if possible, and throws otherwise.

    1. If constructor is not given, set it to %Temporal.YearMonth%.
    2. If overflow is not given, set it to "constrain".
    3. Assert: overflow is one of "constrain" or "reject".
    4. If Type(item) is Object, then
      1. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot, then
        1. Return item.
      2. Let calendar be ? Get(item, "calendar").
      3. If calendar is undefined, set calendar to ? GetISO8601Calendar().
      4. Set calendar to ? ToTemporalCalendar(calendar).
      5. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, "month", "year" ).
      6. Let result be ? ToTemporalYearMonthFields(item, fieldNames).
      7. Return TODO: create via calendar.yearMonthFromFields.
    5. Let string be ? ToString(item).
    6. Let result be ? ParseTemporalYearMonthString(string).
    7. Let referenceISODay be 1.
    8. TODO: get referenceISODay from string.
    9. Let calendar be result.[[Calendar]].
    10. If calendar is undefined, set calendar to ? GetISO8601Calendar().
    11. Set calendar to ? ToTemporalCalendar(calendar).
    12. Set result to ? RegulateYearMonth(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]], overflow).
    13. Return ? CreateTemporalYearMonthFromStatic(constructor, result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]], calendar, referenceISODay).

    9.5.2 ToPartialYearMonth ( temporalYearMonthLike, fieldNames )

    1. If Type(temporalYearMonthLike) is not Object, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    2. Let result be ? OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
    3. Let any be false.
    4. For each value property of fieldNames, do
      1. Let value be ? Get(temporalYearMonthLike, property).
      2. If value is not undefined, then
        1. Set any to true.
        2. If property is either "month" or "year", then
          1. Set value to ? ToInteger(value).
        3. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(result, property, value).
    5. If any is false, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    6. Return result.

    9.5.3 RegulateYearMonth ( year, month, overflow )

    1. Assert: year and month are integer Number values.
    2. Assert: overflow is either "constrain" or "reject".
    3. If overflow is "constrain", then
      1. Return ! ConstrainYearMonth(year, month).
    4. If overflow is "reject", then
      1. If ! ValidateYearMonth(year, month) is false, then
        1. Throw a RangeError exception.
      2. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month }.

    9.5.4 ValidateYearMonth ( year, month )

    1. Assert: year and month are integer Number values.
    2. If month < 1 or month > 12, then
      1. Return false.
    3. Return true.

    9.5.5 ValidateYearMonthRange ( year, month )

    1. Assert: year and month are integer Number values.
    2. If year < 271821 or year > 275760, then
      1. Return false.
    3. If year is 271821 and month < 4, then
      1. Return false.
    4. If year is 275760 and month > 9, then
      1. Return false.
    5. Return true.

    9.5.6 BalanceYearMonth ( year, month )

    1. Assert: year and month are integer Number values.
    2. If year is + or , or month is + or , then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    3. Set year to year + floor((month - 1) / 12).
    4. Set month to NonNegativeModulo(month - 1, 12) + 1.
    5. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month }.

    9.5.7 ConstrainYearMonth ( year, month )

    1. Assert: year and month are integer Number values.
    2. Set month to ! ConstrainToRange(month, 1, 12).
    3. Return the Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month }.

    9.5.8 CreateTemporalYearMonth ( isoYear, isoMonth, calendar, referenceISODay [ , newTarget ] )

    1. If ! ValidateDate(isoYear, isoMonth, referenceISODay) is false, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    2. If ! ValidateYearMonthRange(isoYear, isoMonth) is false, then
      1. Throw a RangeError exception.
    3. If newTarget is not given, set it to %Temporal.YearMonth%.
    4. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget, "%Temporal.YearMonth.prototype%", [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]], [[ISOYear]], [[ISOMonth]], [[ISODay]] ).
    5. Set object.[[ISOYear]] to isoYear.
    6. Set object.[[ISOMonth]] to isoMonth.
    7. Set object.[[Calendar]] to calendar.
    8. Set object.[[ISODay]] to referenceISODay.
    9. Return object.

    9.5.9 CreateTemporalYearMonthFromInstance ( yearMonth, isoYear, isoMonth, calendar, refISODay )

    1. Assert: Type(yearMonth) is Object and yearMonth has an [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot.
    2. Assert: ! ValidateYearMonth(isoYear, isoMonth) is true.
    3. Let constructor be ? SpeciesConstructor(yearMonth, %Temporal.YearMonth%).
    4. Let result be ? Construct(constructor, isoYear, isoMonth, calendar, refISODay ).
    5. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(result, [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]]).
    6. Return result.

    9.5.10 CreateTemporalYearMonthFromStatic ( constructor, year, month, calendar, referenceISODay )

    1. Assert: ! ValidateDate(year, month, referenceISODay) is true.
    2. If ! IsConstructor(constructor) is false, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    3. Let result be ? Construct(constructor, year, month, calendar, refISODay ).
    4. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(result, [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]]).
    5. Return result.

    9.5.11 ToTemporalYearMonthFields ( temporalYearMonthLike, fieldNames )

    1. Assert: Type(temporalYearMonthLike) is Object.
    2. Let result be ? OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
    3. For each value property of fieldNames, do
      1. Let value be ? Get(temporalDateLike, property).
      2. If property is either "month", or "year", then
        1. If value is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
        2. Set value to ? ToInteger(value).
      3. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(result, property, value).
    4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(result, "day", 1).
    5. Return result.

    9.5.12 TemporalYearMonthToString ( yearMonth )

    1. Assert: Type(yearMonth) is Object.
    2. Assert: yearMonth has an [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot.
    3. Let year be ! PadYear(yearMonth.[[ISOYear]]).
    4. Let month be yearMonth.[[ISOMonth]] formatted as a two-digit decimal number, padded to the left with a zero if necessary.
    5. Let calendar be ? FormatCalendarAnnotation(yearMonth.[[Calendar]]).
    6. Let result be the string-concatenation of year, the code unit 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS), and month.
    7. If calendar is not the empty String, then
      1. Let day be yearMonth.[[ISODay]] formatted as a two-digit decimal number, padded to the left with a zero if necessary.
      2. Set result to the string-concatenation of result, the code unit 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS), day, and calendar.
    8. Return result.

    10 Temporal.MonthDay Objects

    A Temporal.MonthDay object is an immutable Object that contains Number values corresponding to a particular year and month.

    10.1 The Temporal.MonthDay Constructor

    The Temporal.MonthDay constructor is the %Temporal.MonthDay% intrinsic object. When called as a constructor, it creates and initializes a new Temporal.MonthDay object.

    The Temporal.MonthDay constructor is designed to be subclassable. It may be used as the value of an extends clause of a class definition. Subclass constructors that intend to inherit the specified MonthDay behaviour must include a super call to the %Temporal.MonthDay% constructor to create and initialize subclass instances with the necessary internal slots.

    10.1.1 Temporal.MonthDay ( isoMonth, isoDay [ , calendarLike [ , referenceISOYear ] ] )

    When the Temporal.MonthDay function is called, the following steps are taken:

    1. If NewTarget is undefined, then
      1. Throw a TypeError exception.
    2. If referenceISOYear is not given, then
      1. Set referenceISOYear to 1972.
    3. Let m be ? ToInteger(isoMonth).
    4. Let d be ? ToInteger(isoDay).
    5. If calendarLike is undefined, then
      1. Set calendar to ? GetISO8601Calendar().
    6. Else,
      1. Set calendar to ? ToTemporalCalendar(calendarLike).
    7. Let ref be ? ToInteger(referenceISOYear).
    8. Return ? CreateTemporalMonthDay(m, d, calendar, ref, NewTarget).
     Note
    1972 is the first leap year after the Unix epoch.

    10.2 Properties of the Temporal.MonthDay Constructor

    The value of the [[Prototype]] internal slot of the Temporal.MonthDay constructor is the intrinsic object %Function.prototype%.

    10.3.10 Temporal.MonthDay.prototype.valueOf ( )

    The following steps are taken:

    1. Throw a TypeError exception.

    10.3.11 Temporal.MonthDay.prototype.toDateInYear ( item [ , options ] )

    The toDateInYear method takes two arguments, item and options. The following steps are taken:

    1. Let monthDay be the this value.
    2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(monthDay, [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]]).
    3. Set options to ? NormalizeOptionsObject(options).
    4. Let overflow be ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
    5. Let calendar be monthDay.[[Calendar]].
    6. Let receiverFieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, "day", "month" ).
    7. Let fields be ? ToTemporalMonthDayFields(monthDay, receiverFieldNames).
    8. If Type(item) is Object, then
      1. Let inputFieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, "year" ).
      2. For each value property of inputFieldNames, do
        1. Let value be ? Get(temporalMonthDayLike, property).
        2. If property is "year", and value is undefined, then
          1. Throw a TypeError exception.
        3. Let value be ? ToInteger(value).
        4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, property, value).
    9. Else,
      1. Let y be ? ToInteger(item).
      2. Perform ! Set(fields, "year", y, false).
    10. TODO: create via calendar.dateFromFields. Return ? CreateTemporalDate(date.[[Year]], date.[[Month]], date.[[Day]]).

    10.3.12 Temporal.MonthDay.prototype.getFields ( )

    The following steps are taken:

    4. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, "day", "month" ).
    5. Let fields be ? ToTemporalMonthDayFields(monthDay, fieldNames).

    7. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoYear", (monthDay.[[ISOYear]])).
